<TITLE> AG Alam receives death threat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 19 (bdnews24.com)Attorney General Mahbubey Alam received a scrap of shroud cloth within hours of the final verdict in the Bangabandhu murder case on Thursday, the second death threat since the appeals process began. Mahbubey Alam told bdnews24.com said he received a package with a three-page letter signed by a little-known group 'Jamia Islami al Halhalia Bangladesh'. "Inside was also a scrap of shroud cloth, meant as a death threat." "The letter asked 'Why are you crying for Sheikh Mujib and (his son) Sheikh Russell?'" said Alam. It also said "Faruk and Rashid did their patriotic duty in killing them," the attorney general quoted. He said the letter warned that Nov 22 would be "the last day of the attorney general" if the death sentences were upheld on Thursday. Shahbagh police officer Monir Hossain told bdnews24.com the attorney general's office received the package at around 3.30pm. The attorney general's assistant Kabir Ahmed filed a general diary at around 4.30pm, he said. The attorney general previously received an anonymous letter on Oct 26, threatening him and his family with death if the convicts in the Bangabandhu murder case were not released. That letter was also sent to his office in the afternoon. bd
